lyze QE2 with a simple thermal model and data from both the\nNASA IRTF SpeX instrument and NEOWISE mission. We determine an albedo between\n0.05 and 0.10 and thermal inertia between 0 and 425 J m$^{-2}$ s$^{-1/2}$\nK$^{-1}$. We find that overall the simple thermal model is able to well\nconstrain the properties of QE2, however we find that model uncertainties can\nbe influenced by topography, viewing geometry, and the wavelength range of data\nused.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 12 Jan 2023 15:15:14 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-01-13"}
